#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:4
msgid "Rich Hickey 2011-10-15"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Clojure and its communication forums are run by, and for, people who make "
"things. Most messages should have one of these forms:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:13
msgid "I made something - here is my contribution"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:14
msgid ""
"I am trying to use the thing someone made and am having trouble, please help."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:15
msgid "I can help you with that thing someone made."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:16
msgid "I am trying to make something and am having trouble, please help."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:17
msgid "I can help you make something."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:19
msgid "They are not the place for opinion pieces and diatribes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:21
msgid ""
"They are not the place for advocacy about what 'ought' to be made. If you "
"think something ought to be made, then make it. Otherwise, respect others "
"peoples' right to choose what they do with their time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:23
msgid ""
"Occasionally, there may be disagreements about how something has been, or "
"will be, made. These disagreements should take the form of technical "
"arguments. To make a technical argument that gets (and gives!) respect:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:25
msgid "Keep it short"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:26
msgid "Stick to the facts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:27
msgid "Use logic"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:28
msgid "Leave people out of it"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:33
msgid ""
"Avoid rhetorical devices: ** Superfluous or opinion-laden adjectives ** "
"Claims to speak for the community, or that everyone agrees with you.  ** "
"Threats of what will happen unless things go your way ** Any flavor of 'the "
"sky is falling'"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:35
msgid ""
"If you are not the one making something, you should restrict your input to "
"very short technical arguments supporting your position. If someone has "
"already made your point, just +1 it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:37
msgid "Please keep your posts short."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/content/community/etiquette.adoc:39
msgid ""
"Ignoring these guidelines fails to respect the time and effort of people who "
"make things, which you should care about if you intend to be one."
msgstr ""

